  abstract = {This paper extends the reach of General Purpose GPU programming by presenting a software architecture that supports efficient fine-grained synchronization over global memory. The key idea is to transform global synchronization into global communication so that conflicts are serialized at the thread block level. With this structure, the threads within each thread block can synchronize using low latency, high-bandwidth local scratchpad memory. To enable this architecture, we implement a scalable and efficient message passing library.},
